        <div n="Y07B083Y">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">by D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Sheridan.</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y07B083Y-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-1" n="1">Would you that Delville I describe,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-2" n="2">Believe me Sir I will not gibe.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-3" n="3">For Who woud be satirical</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-4" n="4">Upon a thing so very small.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-5" n="5"><lb/>You scarce upon the borders enter,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-6" n="6">Before you're at the very center,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-7" n="7">A single Crow can make it night,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-8" n="8">When o'er your farm she takes her flight.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-9" n="9">Yet in this narrow compass we,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-10" n="10">Observe a great variety.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-11" n="11">Both Walks, Walls, meadows, &amp; parterres,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-12" n="12">Windows, &amp; doors, &amp; Rooms &amp; Stairs,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-13" n="13">And hills, &amp; dales, &amp; woods &amp; fields,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-14" n="14">And hay, &amp; grass, &amp; Corn it yields,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-15" n="15">All to your haggard brought so cheap in,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-16" n="16">Without the mowing, or the Reaping,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-17" n="17">A Razor tho to say it I am loth,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-18" n="18">Woud shave you &amp; your meadows both.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-19" n="19">Tho small the farm, yet heres a House,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-20" n="20">Full large to entertain a Mouse,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-21" n="21">But where a Rat is dreaded more,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-22" n="22">Than savage Caledonian Boar,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-23" n="23">For if 'tis enterd by a Rat,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-24" n="24">There is no room to bring a Cat.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-25" n="25">A little Rivulet seems to steal,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-26" n="26">Down thro a thing you call a Vale,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-27" n="27">Like tears adown a wrinkled cheek,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-28" n="28">Or rain a·long a blade of Leak,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-29" n="29">And this you call your sweet meander,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-30" n="30">Which might be suck·d up by a Gander,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-31" n="31">Could he but force his nether bill,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-32" n="32">To scoop the Channel of the rill,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-33" n="33">I'm sure you·d make a mighty Clutter,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-34" n="34">Where it as big as City gutter.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-35" n="35">Next come I to your Kitchen garden,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-36" n="36">Which one poor slug, woud fare but hard in,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-37" n="37">And round this garden is a Walk,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-38" n="38">No longer than a Taylors Chalk,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-39" n="39">Thus I compute what space is in it,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-40" n="40">A snail creep·s round it in a minute.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-41" n="41">One Lettuce makes a shift to squeeze,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-42" n="42">Up thro a tuft you call your Trees.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-43" n="43">And once a year a single Rose,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-44" n="44">Peep·s thro the bud, but never blows,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-45" n="45">It cannot blow for want of Room.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-46" n="46">In vain you may expect its Bloom.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-47" n="47">In short, in all your boasted seat,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-Y07B083Y-line-48" n="48">There's nothing but yourself is great.</l>
          </lg>
